{
  "name": "Bhai Jaspal Singh (USA)",
  "url": "https://kirtansewa.net/index.php/bhai-jaspal-singh-usa/",
  "image_url": "https://cdn.kirtansewa.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/21230624/Screenshot84-Color-Restored.jpg",
  "body": [
    "Bhai Jaspal Singh Ji has Kirtan coursing through his veins as he belongs to the illustrious ‘Zakhmi’ family. His father, Bhai Gursharan Singh Ji was the younger brother of Bhai Dharam Singh Zakhmi and used to accompany him on tabla. Bhai Jaspal Singh Ji was born to Mata Jasbir Kaur Ji in Adampur, Punjab on 20th December 1952. He developed a keen interest in Kirtan and classical music from a very young age and this was observed by both his father and grandfather, Bhai Daulat Singh Ji. This led to his initiation and formal training under their guidance at the tender age of five. He was also sent to the Kirtan Vidhyala in Nangal run by renowned Prof. Darshan Singh Komal for further training. At the age of 16, he came under the wing of one of the main pillars of Gurmat Sangeet, Bhai Avtar Singh Ji, whose roots in Gurmat Sangeet date back to the time of Guru Arjan Dev Ji. Bhai Jaspal Singh Ji acquired a vast repertoire of old Dhrupad compositions from Bhai Avtar Singh Ji and he is adept at performing in many difficult ‘taals’.",
    "A true musician never stops learning and similarly, Bhai Jaspal Singh Ji yearned for more knowledge. This led him to learn from some other notable figures in the field of music including Ghazal maestro, Mehndi Hassan and Hindustani classical vocalist, Lakshmi Shankar. This allowed him to tap into his creativity and to develop a unique style of his own that set him apart from his contemporaries. He was able to blend music with the Shabad in such a manner that it would transport the listener to a new world of experience. Bhai Sahib is known for experimenting with various instruments in his Kirtan and this uniqueness allowed him to captivate listeners around the world. He would always have the best musicians providing accompaniment to his melodious voice.",
    "Bhai Jaspal Singh Ji immigrated to England in 1969 along with his parents. While living in the United Kingdom, he took part in many Raag Darbars and enthralled the Sangat with his Kirtan. When Bhai Jaspal Singh Ji was in his early 20s, he experienced a defining point in his life when Sant Isher Singh Ji of Rara Sahib visited London. He was enraptured with Sant Isher Singh Ji’s personality and through his company and blessings, Bhai Jaspal Singh Ji found his true purpose. He embarked on a journey to share the divine Shabad of the Gurus and Bhagats. Bhai Jaspal Singh Ji travelled the world to share his experiences and to inspire others to realise their potential and attain these spiritual experiences through Gurbani. Through his unique blend of instruments in his Kirtan and mastery in Katha, he was able to spread this message far and wide. He also has a great command in English allowing him to capture the attention of the youth as well. Bhai Jaspal Singh Ji also had his own exclusive TV Show on Zee Punjabi and ETC Punjabi for 7 years which was telecasted in Asia, UK and North America.",
    "The information above was gathered from various sources. If anyone has more recordings of Bhai Jaspal Singh Ji to share, please contact us."
  ],
